  "text": "Apache Kafka's plugin/extension loading system is implemented in the org.apache.kafka.connect.runtime.isolation package. The system provides classloading isolation for plugins and interface-based dependency injection for Connector, Converter, and HeaderConverter plugins.\n\nCore Architecture:\n\n1. **PluginClassLoader (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginClassLoader.java)**: A custom URLClassLoader that extends Java's URLClassLoader to provide child-first classloading semantics. It isolates plugin classes from the main classpath, allowing multiple versions of dependencies to coexist. The loadClass method uses PluginUtils.shouldLoadInIsolation() to determine which classes to load in isolation vs. delegate to the parent classloader.\n\n2. **DelegatingClassLoader (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/DelegatingClassLoader.java)**: A parent classloader that delegates loading to individual PluginClassLoaders for their respective plugins. It maintains a map of plugin loaders and handles version-aware plugin loading through the pluginLoader() and connectorLoader() methods.\n\n3. **Plugins (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/Plugins.java)**: The central orchestrator for plugin discovery, instantiation, and dependency injection. It implements:\n   - initLoaders(): Initializes the plugin discovery process using ReflectionScanner or ServiceLoaderScanner\n   - newConverter(): Factory method for instantiating and configuring Converter plugins\n   - newHeaderConverter(): Factory method for instantiating and configuring HeaderConverter plugins\n   - newConnector(): Factory method for instantiating Connector plugins\n   - newVersionedPlugin(): Generic factory for versioned plugin instantiation with configuration injection\n\n4. **Plugin Discovery via Reflection & ServiceLoader**:\n   - **PluginScanner (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginScanner.java)**: Abstract base class for plugin discovery. Implements discoverPlugins() which discovers plugins from multiple sources and handles JDBC driver loading via ServiceLoader.\n   - **ReflectionScanner (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ReflectionScanner.java)**: Uses ClassGraph library for reflection-based scanning to find all concrete implementations of plugin interfaces (Converter, HeaderConverter, SinkConnector, SourceConnector, Transformation, Predicate). Instantiates each discovered class via reflection to determine version information.\n   - **ServiceLoaderScanner (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ServiceLoaderScanner.java)**: Uses Java's ServiceLoader mechanism to discover plugins that have META-INF/services manifests, providing better performance than ReflectionScanner.\n\n5. **Plugin Metadata & Descriptors**:\n   - **PluginType (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginType.java)**: Enum defining all plugin types (SOURCE, SINK, CONVERTER, HEADER_CONVERTER, TRANSFORMATION, PREDICATE, CONFIGPROVIDER, REST_EXTENSION, CONNECTOR_CLIENT_CONFIG_OVERRIDE_POLICY)\n   - **PluginDesc (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginDesc.java)**: Generic descriptor holding plugin class, version, type, and classloader information\n   - **PluginScanResult (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginScanResult.java)**: Container for all discovered plugins organized by type\n\nInterface-Based Dependency Injection:\n\nThe system uses Java interfaces as extension points:\n\n1. **Connector Interface (connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/connector/Connector.java)**: Abstract base class that all connectors must extend. Provides initialize(ConnectorContext) method for receiving the runtime context, and abstract methods for start/stop/taskConfigs that plugins implement.\n\n2. **SourceConnector (connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/source/SourceConnector.java)** and **SinkConnector (connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/sink/SinkConnector.java)**: Abstract subclasses of Connector for pull and push connectors respectively. The system discovers implementations via getClassesImplementing() or getSubclasses() reflection.\n\n3. **Converter Interface (connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/Converter.java)**: Plugin interface for data serialization/deserialization. The Plugins.newConverter() method instantiates converters and calls their configure(Map, boolean) method with configuration derived from the worker config.\n\n4. **HeaderConverter Interface (connect/api/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/HeaderConverter.java)**: Similar to Converter but specifically for message headers. The Plugins.newHeaderConverter() method handles instantiation and configuration injection.\n\nDependency Injection Mechanism:\n\nThe system injects configuration and context dependencies through method calls:\n- Configuration is passed via configure() methods on Configurable plugins\n- ConnectorContext is passed to Connectors via initialize() method\n- ClassLoader isolation is injected via LoaderSwap (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/LoaderSwap.java), which swaps the thread context classloader during plugin initialization\n- Version requirements are resolved and injected via VersionRange during plugin loading\n\nSupporting Infrastructure:\n\n- **PluginUtils (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginUtils.java)**: Provides shouldLoadInIsolation() to determine which packages are isolated, and other utility methods for plugin path discovery and version handling\n- **ClassLoaderFactory (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/ClassLoaderFactory.java)** and **PluginClassLoaderFactory**: Factory interfaces for creating classloaders\n- **PluginDiscoveryMode (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/PluginDiscoveryMode.java)**: Enum controlling whether to use SERVICE_LOAD, ONLY_SCAN, or HYBRID discovery modes\n- **VersionedPluginLoadingException (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/isolation/VersionedPluginLoadingException.java)**: Exception for version range constraint violations\n\nThe overall flow: initLoaders() → discoverPlugins() → (ReflectionScanner or ServiceLoaderScanner).scanPlugins() → PluginDesc creation → newConverter/newConnector instantiation → configure() injection → plugin ready to use with isolated classloader."
}

